The Rhodians had unfortunately for themselves attempted to me- diate between the Romans and Macedonians. The war disturbed their commerce, and they did not by any means wish to see the Romans victorious. as their independence was owing to the balance of power between the two. So, sorgetting the enormous (lisproporiion between the power of the Romans and their own, they came forward impetuously and offered to mediate with Philip in favour of the Romans. Their language was just as offensive to the Romans as a proposal from Holland to Germany might have been during the late war, offering to get the French to make peace.
